
[1]inveigh

   INVEIGH, v.i. inva'y. [L. inveho, to bear, throw or bring on or
   against; in and veho, to carry.] To exclaim or rail against; to utter
   censorious and bitter language against any one; to reproach; with
   against. The author inveighed sharply against the vices of the clergy
   in his age. Men inveigh against the follies of fashion.
